TestInstance.PlainTextDescription: The order fulfillment process is carried out by a sellerâ€™s organization which includes two departments: the sales department and the warehouse and distribution department. The purchase order received by warehouse and distribution is checked against the stock. This operation is carried out automatically by the ERP system of warehouse and distribution, which queries the warehouse database. If the product is in stock, it is retrieved from the warehouse before sales confirm the order. Next sales emit an invoice and wait for the payment, while the product is shipped from within warehouse and distribution. The process completes with the order archival in the sales department. If the product is not in stock, the ERP system within warehouse and distribution checks the raw materials availability by accessing the suppliers catalog. Once the raw materials have been obtained the warehouse and distribution department takes care of manufacturing the product. The process completes with the purchase order being confirmed and archived by the sales department.
